From: Andre Klapper <a9016009@gmx.de>
Date: Tue, 13 Jan 2026 05:30:19 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 20/50] PhutilConsoleProgressBar: Fix invalid float array key
 type

Summary: `floor()` returns the next lowest integer value as float. Array index keys need to be int or string, so cast to int.

Test Plan: Run static code analysis.

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, mainframe98

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, mainframe98

Subscribers: tobiaswiese, valerio.bozzolan, Matthew, Cigaryno

Differential Revision: https://we.phorge.it/D26675
---
 src/console/PhutilConsoleProgressBar.php | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/console/PhutilConsoleProgressBar.php b/src/console/PhutilConsoleProgressBar.php
index 43fbd0de4ec1..6c44e7767dfe 100644
--- a/src/console/PhutilConsoleProgressBar.php
+++ b/src/console/PhutilConsoleProgressBar.php
@@ -134,7 +134,7 @@ final class PhutilConsoleProgressBar extends Phobject {
       '-',
       '~',
     );
-    $frac_char = $frac_map[floor($bar_frac * count($frac_map))];
+    $frac_char = $frac_map[(int)floor($bar_frac * count($frac_map))];
 
     $pattern = "[%-{$max_width}.{$max_width}s] % 5s%%";
     $out = sprintf(
